    <div class="container center col s12 m4">
        <p class="light">
            Fractal Hexagon is a network of independent people working on various projects, some of which include webdesign, storywriting, and eventually video game development. The co-founders of Fractal Hexagon are Dasporal, Haruto and Planetary, and we have worked on various projects, including the Snowflake theme for TweetDeck, Redlight for YouTube (experimental). We are working on a few light novel series, including which the Arch Nova Renegades series, The Providence Online series, and the World;Slicers series. We seek to create a video game based on The Providence Online novels; it will be a T-RPG game currently known as the project name SHARDSTREAM. However, we are for the most college students, meaning we have limited financial means, and little time on our hands, making it difficult to find time to work on the project. We want to shift to other media, such as an in-the-works webcomic under the name Everwinter, and a computer graphics webseries known as &lt;WORLD/SWITCH&gt;; taking over a discontinued light novel project. Fractal Hexagon is open to anyone, at least anyone we know. This is an informal small group (as such, this website is mostly for internal use and referencing of our projects). There are technically no application requirement, except maybe you need to be a developer, a webdesigner, a writer, or an artist of any kind, and no particular order or contribution is asked. It is mostly about people helping each other out <em>if they want to</em>. That also means unless we ask a third-party, we are not looking to hire for a retributed job.</p>
